HEADWORD: Facture
<hw>Fac"ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>facture</ets> a making, invoice, L. <ets>factura</ets> a making.
See <er>Fact</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or manner of making
or doing anything; -- now used of a literary, musical, or pictorial
production.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>An invoice or bill of
parcels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>faculae</ent>⟦br⟧
